- cs.CG (Computational Geometry): The problem of online minimum cost matching on the line involves geometric objects (points on the real line) and their distances, which are typical topics in computational geometry. 
- cs.DM (Discrete Mathematics): The paper deals with a combinatorial optimization problem (minimum cost matching) and presents a new approach based on a recourse model, which can be seen as a form of dynamic programming. 
- cs.AL (Algorithms): The paper presents a new algorithmic solution to the problem of online minimum cost matching on the line, which is a classic problem in algorithms research.
